The paper deals with the construction of network topologies in wireless ad-hoc networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves the use of graph theory and optimization techniques, which are common in the subfield of distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in random networks, which involves the use of probabilistic analysis and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of preserving connectivity in the network, which is a common problem in the subfield of social networks (cs.SI).
